div.p:
On following morning we met again with same group. Foreign Minister read from
                    prepared notes statement that Cabinet had instructed him to make re his
                    understanding of my answers to questions raised previous day, as follows: 


                            Verbatim text.



“(1) Economic aid can be separated from military aid;

“(2) It is understood that acceptance of economic aid will not
                                deprive US from maintaining a policy of positive neutrality;

“(3) Economic aid does not in any way hurt Arab country;

“(4) The schemes to be financed under this Doctrine are those
                                which we would propose and which would be agreed upon by the
                                US;

“(5) The funds to be spent by the Sudanese Government on the
                                projects agreed upon would be placed at the disposal of the Sudanese
                                Government;

“(6) The technical experts involved will be limited only to those
                                required for the agreed projects;

“(7) Acceptance of economic aid does not bar us from accepting
                                from other countries including the USSR.” End verbatim text.
